author: @war0nstupidity767
text: I will be very honest, this guy is very good in theory & algorithm (books) but he needs to brush up his coding skills and invest more time with Python. The way he struggles to ran those 14 lines of codes shows it all.He lacks confidence with flask but gained it on algo.   A good interviewer should try to know both strength & weakness but here he appreciation "breaking records" sounds like a script. A professional will start with greeting and ends with a smile rest between is inter- view. It's not just about choosing to hire but to tell the candidate about his strength & weaknesses, which will help him in future. I have took lots of campus interviews and everyone will be good in theories.

author: @NiteshKumar-wp7fe
text: The guy Sumit is awesome but this is my humble request to the interviewer pls don‚Äôt ask too much so called tech/programming stuff if you‚Äôre hiring for data science or Analytics profile. A candidate should be first evaluated based on his/her critical and problem solving approach. Any resource who is strong at maths and critical thinking side can be trained on any r/Python languages or tolls very quickly. Remember tools/languages are only enabler it will not help in structuring the real business problems. These all rest api and and Python implement can be done using small googling but solving a real business problem is an art which comes slowly with time and dedication. Pls ask more business use cases / hypothetical business problems to candidates instead of only focusing on tech or tooling

author: @sujitkumar-pr3rr
text: It's good interview. But at 39:30 NB theorem formula is incorrect and at 41:40 he is saying we will do Pass/(Pass + Fail) so that value come's in the range of [0,1]. First of all, the P(Pass/F1=A,F2=C) value already very small and probability is always in range of  [0,1], so there is no need to do this thing i.e. Pass/(Pass + Fail) bcoz it will make P value more smaller. We don't want small value that's why we use log so that my value not become much less.  Congratulation for the job :)
